New Records: Spencer Strider now has 424 strikeouts in his first 50 career starts, the most since 1893.
Key Match Events: Austin Riley homered in the first to open up the scoring and hit a sacrifice fly in the third to bring in Ronald Acuna Jr.
Kevin Pillar doubled in the fourth to score Marcell Ozuna
Matt Olson will have to wait one more game to break the Braves’ single-season home run record
Spencer Strider struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Acuña Jr. responded to booing fans by raising both arms and signaling with his hands to bring it on
Manager Brian Snitker said, 'We've checked one box'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title
The Phillies lead the NL wild card and the teams could face each other in October

The Braves have seemingly made winning the East a rite of September since the 1990s and this year’s team looks loaded enough to win their third World Series since moving from Milwaukee to Atlanta in 1966
